  "description": {
    "lang": "eng",
    "value": "Cross-site Scripting (XSS) - Stored in GitHub repository allegroai/clearml-server prior to 1.13.0.\n\nReason for inclusion in AVID: CVE-2023-6778 is a stored cross-site scripting vulnerability in allegroai/clearml-server (prior to 1.13.0). ClearML-server is a web service used to manage AI experiments and pipelines, making this a vulnerability in a software component commonly used in general-purpose AI stacks. This aligns with software supply-chain issues in AI systems (dependencies/runtimes serving AI workloads). It is a security vulnerability (XSS) with documented impact signals. The report provides explicit CVE details, affected artifact, and references."
  },
